Package: VisuStatR
Type: Package
Title: Visualizing Statistics on Images in R
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Christoph Harmel
Maintainer: Christoph Harmel <christoph.harmel@icloud.com>
Description: VisuStatR fills an important gap to visually assess time-dependent summary statistics, which allows validation and critical interpretation of obtained quantities in comparison to the raw image data.
    By its convenient graphical user interface, VisuStatR is directly accessible to biological researchers and represents a useful tool for the interpretation of live-cell microscopy data. 
License: MIT+ 
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.6),
    tidyverse,
    grid,
    gridExtra,
    rlang,
    magick,
    cowplot,
    parallel,
    foreach,
    doSNOW,
    plotly
Imports:
    Rmisc,
    facetscales,
    ggecho
RoxygenNote: 7.1.2
